just not today, all right?

22:15.501 --> 22:16.901
- Can't you understand that?
- Before we leave,

22:16.903 --> 22:18.636
I just wanted to confirm
the mileage fees.

22:18.638 --> 22:20.338
Get mom, please.

22:20.340 --> 22:21.906
If you could fill out
the method of payment form,

22:21.908 --> 22:23.574
considering your situation.

22:23.576 --> 22:25.376
It's best we handle this
on the front end.

22:25.378 --> 22:27.445
- Estelle?!
- Guy tells me to drive, I drive.

22:27.447 --> 22:29.080
I know,
but he happens to be insane.

22:29.082 --> 22:30.815
Take my dad's stuff
out of the car right now,

22:30.817 --> 22:31.982
or else I'm calling the police.

22:31.984 --> 22:33.751
- And tell them what?
- Estelle!

22:33.753 --> 22:35.820
- What's going on here?
- -Hold on!

22:35.822 --> 22:38.489
I'll be down in a second!
I'm putting my face on!

22:38.491 --> 22:39.957
Then don't get involved.
Move out of the way.

22:39.959 --> 22:42.059
Listen, come on,
what are you doing?

22:42.061 --> 22:45.096
- Dad, do not get in that car!
- -Lady, take it easy.

22:45.098 --> 22:47.465
I can do this all day.
Want me to keep doing this?

22:47.467 --> 22:49.633
I will do this all...
Really funny.

22:49.635 --> 22:52.103
I'm taking the keys!
I'm taking the keys!

22:52.105 --> 22:53.838
Brian, do something!

23:23.101 --> 23:25.669
Would you put this in, please?

23:25.671 --> 23:26.937
What is this?

23:29.007 --> 23:31.776
<i>Blue-footed booby.</i>

23:31.778 --> 23:33.944
This is so much more pleasant

23:33.946 --> 23:36.046
than travelling with a stranger.

23:36.048 --> 23:38.082
<i>Great-tailed grackle.</i>

23:38.084 --> 23:40.785
Don't you have a job?

23:40.787 --> 23:43.788
I brought the job with me
in my briefcase right there.

23:43.790 --> 23:45.589
Hope you guys don't mind
if your chauffeur

23:45.591 --> 23:47.491
does a little side work.

23:49.028 --> 23:51.429
No one forced you
to take us, you know?

23:51.431 --> 23:53.898
- I'm not saying that you did.
- It sounds like you are.

23:53.900 --> 23:55.966
Honey, can you turn that down
a little bit, please?

23:55.968 --> 23:58.035
- I like it!
- It's too loud!

23:58.037 --> 23:59.537
You used to like it, too.

23:59.539 --> 24:02.139
I love it.
But it's too loud, okay?

24:02.141 --> 24:03.974
I need to use the bathroom.

24:03.976 --> 24:05.509
Right now?

24:05.511 --> 24:07.511
I have to go, damn it.

24:07.513 --> 24:10.080
We... just left.

24:10.082 --> 24:11.816
<i>Dickcissel.</i>

24:17.924 --> 24:19.790
<i>Dunlin.</i>

24:22.962 --> 24:25.563
<i>Eastern whip-poor-will.</i>

24:30.802 --> 24:32.970
All right, we're here.

24:32.972 --> 24:34.738
Do you want to get out
and stretch your legs?

24:34.740 --> 24:36.106
- No, I'm good.
- Are you sure?

24:36.108 --> 24:38.008
- Sure as a pickle.
- Okay.

24:39.044 --> 24:40.578
Here we go.

24:43.181 --> 24:45.149
- Hey.
- -<i> Hey.</i>

24:45.151 --> 24:46.851
- It's gonna be fine.
<i>- Look, if you're doing this</i>

24:46.853 --> 24:48.686
<i>- to prove some kind of point...</i>
- I'm not.

24:48.688 --> 24:50.621
We're gonna drive west
for another day.

24:50.623 --> 24:52.656
They're gonna run out of steam,
and I'm gonna have them back

24:52.658 --> 24:54.158
by tomorrow night, okay?

24:54.160 --> 24:55.993
<i>I doubt it's gonna be that easy.</i>

24:55.995 --> 24:57.895
You keep Annie away
from what's-his-face,

24:57.897 --> 24:59.864
and I'll have your dad back
by the end of the weekend, deal?

24:59.866 --> 25:02.666
- You have a bathroom?
- It's in the garage.

25:02.668 --> 25:05.002
- But it's for customers only...
- Oh, no, he's with me.

25:05.004 --> 25:07.071
- He's just gonna keep walking?
- I'm buying something.

25:07.073 --> 25:08.973
- I'm gonna be a customer.
- Okay.

25:11.877 --> 25:14.845
Is that all?
Because that's like $6.95

25:14.847 --> 25:16.680
and we have a $10 minimum.

25:16.682 --> 25:18.215
Ten bucks to use the bathroom?

25:18.217 --> 25:20.851
Mm-hmm.
It's a company policy.

25:24.022 --> 25:25.589
That was my father-in-law.

25:25.591 --> 25:27.224
Mm-hmm?

25:27.226 --> 25:30.628
I'm driving him to Oregon
so that he can kill himself.

25:34.533 --> 25:36.000
We good here?

25:50.682 --> 25:53.551
<i>Hey, it's Nick.
Leave a message.</i>

25:53.553 --> 25:54.952
<i>Or don't.</i>

25:54.954 --> 25:58.255
- Hey, bud.
- Hey, bud.

25:58.257 --> 25:59.890
It's dad.

25:59.892 --> 26:02.993
I'm just driving through
Pennsylvania right now.

26:02.995 --> 26:06.830
I was thinking about
when we went to Columbus

26:06.832 --> 26:08.866
for your campus visit.

26:08.868 --> 26:12.336
So, I was just thinking
about you, bud.

26:12.338 --> 26:15.739
All right.
Call me back when you can.

26:24.583 --> 26:26.817
What time is it?

26:26.819 --> 26:29.720
Um, just after 10:00.

26:29.722 --> 26:31.655
Do you need a break?

26:31.657 --> 26:32.957
Nope. I'm fine.

26:32.959 --> 26:34.158
You sure?

26:34.160 --> 26:35.926
Sure as a pickle.

26:35.928 --> 26:38.228
'Cause I can take that wheel
for a bit,

26:38.230 --> 26:39.730
if you want me to.

26:39.732 --> 26:41.832
Okay, you cannot drive, Estelle.

26:41.834 --> 26:44.802
Oh, I can drive.
I can drive just fine.

26:44.804 --> 26:46.670
State of New York disagrees.

26:50.742 --> 26:53.777
No doctor's ever
going to approve this.

26:53.779 --> 26:55.879
What's that?

26:55.881 --> 26:58.782
I read all those pamphlets
he's been collecting for years.

26:58.784 --> 27:02.853
They all say
you have to be dying.

27:06.358 --> 27:07.691
Why are you here?

27:12.163 --> 27:13.998
It's where I'm supposed to be.

27:39.924 --> 27:41.291
Can I help you?

27:41.293 --> 27:43.293
Yeah, I'd like two rooms,
please.

27:43.295 --> 27:45.829
Can't do it.
Only one room left.

27:45.831 --> 27:48.198
Oh, god no,
that's not gonna work.

27:48.200 --> 27:49.867
It's a good room.

27:49.869 --> 27:52.202
Two queen beds,
laundry room adjacent.

27:52.204 --> 27:54.338
A view of the fire pit,
which is currently closed.

27:54.340 --> 27:56.206
Yeah, okay, no, no, thank you.

27:56.208 --> 27:59.910
Okay, then, see you
in a couple of hours.

27:59.912 --> 28:02.312
I'm sorry, what?

28:02.314 --> 28:04.081
Hot air balloon fest
up in Toledo.

28:04.083 --> 28:07.351
Everything's booked.
They all end up back here.

28:59.003 --> 29:00.437
Hey, sweetie.

29:00.439 --> 29:02.906
I don't want to talk about it.

29:02.908 --> 29:07.044
Okay.
You want some coffee?

29:09.314 --> 29:11.915
- Black.
- All right.

29:17.322 --> 29:20.824
All right, listen to me,
guys can still care about you

29:20.826 --> 29:23.393
even when they do
really stupid shit.

29:23.395 --> 29:25.329
You should have seen the stuff
your dad used to do

29:25.331 --> 29:27.030
before he got me.

29:27.032 --> 29:28.866
Colt already had me.

29:28.868 --> 29:30.367
Well, then you know what?

29:30.369 --> 29:34.872
He was a very...
Stupid and lucky boy.

29:34.874 --> 29:37.074
- I don't wanna cheer anymore.
- Why?

29:37.076 --> 29:39.076
Because I'd have
to cheer for him.

29:39.078 --> 29:41.145
Oh, babe, that's silly.
I don't know why you'd have

29:41.147 --> 29:43.914
to give up something you love
because of all of this.

29:43.916 --> 29:45.482
Listen, trust me, okay?

29:45.484 --> 29:50.287
A month from now,
this is gonna be so much easier.

29:50.289 --> 29:51.789
Dad hates me.

29:51.791 --> 29:53.490
Oh, gosh, no.
Come here.

29:53.492 --> 29:57.161
No, he doesn't.
No, he doesn't hate you.

29:57.163 --> 30:01.999
His frustrations have
a whole other focus right now.

30:49.280 --> 30:51.481
- I got a salmon salad.
- Thank you.

30:51.483 --> 30:53.383
- Chicken salad.
- Thank you.

30:53.385 --> 30:57.054
And a Patty melt with extra
onion rings and slaw.

30:59.390 --> 31:01.325
Mm, this looks good.

31:01.327 --> 31:03.427
This is dry.

31:03.429 --> 31:05.229
Oh, honey, it'll be fine.

31:05.231 --> 31:06.997
I said Mayo.

31:09.367 --> 31:12.169
Okay.
I'll get you some Mayo.

31:16.507 --> 31:20.377
Can I have some Mayo,
please, on the side?

31:20.379 --> 31:22.312
- Is this a good diner?
- Excellent diner.

31:22.314 --> 31:24.548
Really?
Oh, well, that was lucky.

31:24.550 --> 31:27.351
We picked a good place.
What do you normally get here?

31:27.353 --> 31:29.353
Everything's good,
but I like the meatloaf.

31:29.355 --> 31:31.622
Oh, I love meatloaf.
We didn't get any today.

31:31.624 --> 31:33.190
Hey, let me see
if I can help out...

31:33.192 --> 31:35.559
No. Let her talk.

31:35.561 --> 31:38.095
Ten years ago,
I would've said something.

31:38.097 --> 31:39.529
I would have been
over there by now.

31:39.531 --> 31:42.099
Hey, if it bothers you,
then go over there.

31:42.101 --> 31:44.268
- There's no point.
- Go take her by the hand.

31:44.270 --> 31:46.069
Maybe this is what
you both need.

31:46.071 --> 31:48.105
She's the one
who still has needs.

31:48.107 --> 31:51.208
Well, you know...
There...

31:51.210 --> 31:54.478
There are different ways to...

31:54.480 --> 31:55.913
Handle that.

31:55.915 --> 31:57.214
What?

31:57.216 --> 32:01.151
Have you ever, like,
considered Viagra?

32:01.153 --> 32:04.321
Have <i> you</i> ever
considered Viagra?!

32:04.323 --> 32:06.256
Don't tell me what my needs are.

32:06.258 --> 32:07.658
You talk to me when
your hard-ons

32:07.660 --> 32:09.293
- turn to mashed potatoes!
- All right...

32:09.295 --> 32:10.928
Back when I was your age,

32:10.930 --> 32:13.030
a light gust of wind,
I was hard as a rock!

32:13.032 --> 32:15.532
I could make that woman bloom
without even dipping my stem in.

32:15.534 --> 32:17.200
Honey, honey, keep it down.

32:17.202 --> 32:19.069
Here's your Mayo.
Okay, here we go.

32:19.071 --> 32:21.104
You remember the summer
that we bought the cabin

32:21.106 --> 32:22.673
and you sent the kids
to your father?

32:22.675 --> 32:24.574
You couldn't keep your hands
off me, could you?

32:24.576 --> 32:27.244
No, Raymond, I couldn't,
but I don't know if Brian

32:27.246 --> 32:29.146
- is really interested...
- We did it every day.

32:29.148 --> 32:30.647
- Every single day.
- Ray?

32:30.649 --> 32:32.616
We did it until the tanagers
started chirping.

32:32.618 --> 32:34.384
Take these pills, please.
And stop bragging.

32:34.386 --> 32:36.553
And this woman
is 12 years my junior.

32:36.555 --> 32:38.288
And I could still get it up!

32:40.491 --> 32:44.127
All I'm saying ray,
is that I think that...

32:44.129 --> 32:46.463
That there are other options.

32:46.465 --> 32:47.464
Besides what?

32:47.466 --> 32:50.067
This trip.

32:50.069 --> 32:51.969
Nobody wants this, ray.

32:54.572 --> 32:57.741
She forgot my dressing,
so I'll be back in a minute.

33:01.612 --> 33:05.349
Do you have any idea how much
this is upsetting your daughter?

33:05.351 --> 33:06.984
Yeah.

33:06.986 --> 33:08.585
Then where the hell is she?

33:08.587 --> 33:10.988
Well, she does have
obligations as a parent.

33:10.990 --> 33:15.125
Bullshit! You all gave up
on me a long time ago!

33:18.563 --> 33:20.197
I'm outta here.

33:24.369 --> 33:26.203
- What happened?
- He's outta here.

33:26.205 --> 33:27.671
What do you mean
he's outta here?

33:27.673 --> 33:29.106
Where's he going?

33:29.108 --> 33:31.475
Raymond?

33:31.477 --> 33:35.479
What are you doing?
Raymond?!

33:35.481 --> 33:39.016
Ray. Ray, where are
you going?!

33:39.018 --> 33:40.617
Don't act like
you can't hear me!

33:40.619 --> 33:43.620
- Where are you going?
- Ray, come on back to the car!

33:43.622 --> 33:45.722
What, you think you're gonna
hitchhike to Oregon?

33:45.724 --> 33:49.326
You hate hitchhikers!
You always have!

33:49.328 --> 33:50.694
You don't even have your pills

33:50.696 --> 33:52.362
or anything else
you need with you.

33:52.364 --> 33:54.464
Come on, let's go back...

33:57.102 --> 34:00.070
You're acting like
a spoiled brat child!

34:00.072 --> 34:02.606
You're a grown man
for Pete's sake.

34:02.608 --> 34:04.541
Hey, honey.
Just calling to check in.

34:04.543 --> 34:09.346
Reminiscing a little bit
about Nick's campus tour.

34:09.348 --> 34:12.114
We're taking the same route.
We're in Illinois.

34:12.117 --> 34:13.550
Now.

34:13.552 --> 34:18.388
Looks the same.
Uh... everything's fine here.

34:18.389 --> 34:21.591
